</ul>



<h2><a name="PROF"></a>Professional organisations in individual countries</h2>


<ul>


<li> Flanders: <a href="http://clif.uia.ac.be/"><b>CLIF</b></a>,
Computational Linguistics in Flanders
<li> France: <a href
="http://www.atala.org"><b>ATALA</b></a>, Association pour le Traitement Automatique des Lagues
<li> Germany:
<ul>
<li><a href ="http://www.dgfs-home.de/"><b>DGfS</b></a>, Deutsche Gesellschaft f&uuml;r Sprachwissenschaft
<li><a href="http://www.dfki.de/~busemann/gi/index.html"><b>Gesellschaft f&uuml;r
Informatik Fachgruppe "Nat&uuml;rlichsprachliche Systeme"</b></a>
</ul>
<li><b>Nordic Computational Linguistics Network</b></a>
-- not really an organisation, but a repository for CL in Nordic countries
<li> The Netherlands: <a href
="http://odur.let.rug.nl/~vannoord/clin/"><b>CLIN</b></a>,
Computational Linguistics in the Netherlands (a conference rather than
an organisation)
<li>Poland: <a href ="http://nlp.ipipan.waw.pl/CLIP/"><b>Computational Linguistics in Poland</b></a>
<li>Slovenia: <a href="http://nl.ijs.si/sdjt/index-en.html"><b>SDJT</b></a>,
The Slovenian Language Technologies Society
<li> Spain: <a href ="http://www.sepln.org/"><b>SEPLN</b></a>,Sociedad
Espa&ntilde;ola para el Procesamiento del Lenguaje Natural  
<li> The United Kingdom: <a href="http://nlp.shef.ac.uk/research/cluk/"><b>CLUK</b></a>
</ul>


